Quote:  The country was all ridges and gullies - so, like the fingers of my hand - and everywhere the trees, and ferns and shrubs grew thickly and were tied together with vines and kareao, and the fairy flax, the kowharawhara, grew in great bunches of long leaves in the tree-forks.
